   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="/jonmsterling/" title="Jon Sterling" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling/" display-uri="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>1</fr:month><fr:day>25</fr:day></fr:date><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
 <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  A]]></fr:tex> be an <fr:link href="/jms-00LA/" title="Idempotent function" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00LA/" display-uri="jms-00LA" type="local">idempotent</fr:link> on a set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> be the subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left \{f{\mathopen {}\left (a\right )\mathclose {}}\,\middle \vert \,a\in  A\right \}\mathclose {}}\subseteq  A]]></fr:tex>, sometimes called the <html:em><fr:link href="/jms-00N6/" title="Direct image" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-00N6/" display-uri="jms-00N6" type="local">direct image</fr:link></html:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>. Then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f\colon  A\to  A]]></fr:tex> factors, by definition, through some unique <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex>, where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}} = f{\mathopen {}\left (x\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x\in  A]]></fr:tex>. We define <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> to be be the subset inclusion.</html:p>
 <html:p>We must check that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r\circ  s = \mathsf {id}_{B}]]></fr:tex>; in other words, we fix <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b\in  B]]></fr:tex> to check that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r{\mathopen {}\left (s{\mathopen {}\left (b\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}} = b]]></fr:tex>. By definition, the subset inclusion <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s\colon  B\to  A]]></fr:tex> takes <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex> to the corresponding element <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[s{\mathopen {}\left (b\right )\mathclose {}}\in  A]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b=f{\mathopen {}\left (s{\mathopen {}\left (b\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. By definition of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r\colon  A \to  B]]></fr:tex>, we therefore have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r{\mathopen {}\left (s{\mathopen {}\left (b\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}=f{\mathopen {}\left (s{\mathopen {}\left (b\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}=b]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
